*quicktime4linux-2.0.4 (23 Jan 2005)

  23 Jan 2005; Jan Brinkmann <luckyduck@gentoo.org>
  +files/2.0.4-external-libs.patch, +quicktime4linux-2.0.4.ebuild:
  new upstream version. fixes #63216.

  16 Jan 2005; Jan Brinkmann <luckyduck@gentoo.org>
  quicktime4linux-2.0.0-r1.ebuild:
  added missing nasm dependency to close bug #59910. removed sparc keyword
  because nasm isnt available for sparc.

  27 Apr 2004; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org>
  quicktime4linux-1.5.5-r1.ebuild, quicktime4linux-1.6.2.ebuild,
  quicktime4linux-2.0.0-r1.ebuild, quicktime4linux-2.0.0.ebuild:
  Add inherit eutils

  25 Feb 2004; Daniel Ahlberg <aliz@gentoo.org>
  quicktime4linux-1.5.5-r1.ebuild, files/quicktime4linux-1.5.5-fPIC.patch:
  Fix fPIC problem. Closing #40555.

  20 Feb 2004; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org>
  quicktime4linux-1.5.5-r1.ebuild, quicktime4linux-1.6.2.ebuild,
  quicktime4linux-2.0.0-r1.ebuild, quicktime4linux-2.0.0.ebuild:
  header fix; media-libs/divx4linux is x86 only

*quicktime4linux-2.0.0-r1 (02 Oct 2003)

  02 Oct 2003; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org> :
  Use external libraries for the most part #25574.  Also add
  a gcc2 patch so the thing will compile ;).

*quicktime4linux-2.0.0 (02 Sep 2003)

  02 Sep 2003; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org> :
  Version bump.

*quicktime4linux-1.6.2 (26 Jul 2003)

  06 Aug 2003; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org> :
  Add ppc filter for gcc flag and add -I for #25574.

  26 Jul 2003; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org> :
  Version bump + NPTL happy header patches.

*quicktime4linux-1.5.5-r1 (13 Jun 2003)
 
  12 Jul 2003; Daniel Ahlberg <aliz@gentoo.org> :
  Added missing changelog entry.

  13 Jun 2003; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org>
  quicktime4linux-1.5.5-r1.ebuild:
  block libquicktime specifically

  13 Jun 2003; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org>
  quicktime4linux-1.5.5-r1.ebuild:
  blocks virtual/quicktime, which libquicktime installs, closing bug #20709 by
  Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org>

  06 Dec 2002; Rodney Rees <manson@gentoo.org> : changed sparc ~sparc keywords
 
*quicktime4linux-1.5.5 (24 May 2002)

  19 Oct 2002; Calum Selkirk <cselkirk@gentoo.org> quicktime4linux-1.5.5-r1 :

  Added ppc to KEYWORDS.

  01 Sep 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org> quicktime4linux-1.5.5-r1 :

  Added libpng as a dependency.  Thanks to twanger@bluetwanger.de (Markus
  Bertheau) in bug #7300.

  26 Jul 2002; Daniel Ahlberg <aliz@gentoo.org> quicktime4linux-1.5.5-r1 :

  Closes #5588 and hopefully #4702 later. Contributions from Fredrik Jagenheim 
  <humming@pobox.com>, Johannes Findeisen <you@hanez.org>
  and Eivind Tagseth <eivindt-gentoo@multinet.no>, thanks!

  24 May 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org>
  quicktime4linux-1.5.5.ebuild files/digest-quicktime4linux-1.5.5 :

  Version bump thanks to gentoo-bugs@devrieze.net (Paul de Vrieze) in bug
  # 1601.  We need an alternative to this library, since the loss of 
  its configure step means no cross-compilation is possible.

*quicktime4linux-1.3 (21 Mar 2002)

  21 Mar 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org> quicktime4linux-1.3.ebuild :

  HTML documentation need not be gzipped.

*quicktime4linux-1.3 (1 Feb 2002)

  1 Feb 2002; G.Bevin <gbevin@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :
  
  Added initial ChangeLog which should be updated whenever the package is
  updated in any way. This changelog is targetted to users. This means that the
  comments should well explained and written in clean English. The details about
  writing correct changelogs are explained in the skel.ChangeLog file which you
  can find in the root directory of the portage repository.
